However, there are many sacraments, and they are not all the same.

223
00:43:04,199 --> 00:43:47,786
As the Apostle Paul says in the book of Hebrews:
"In many ways and at many times in the past, God spoke to our ancestors through the prophets, but in these last days, He has spoken to us through His Son."
Discussing the variety of sacraments, which prepared the future dispensation of Christ and the salvation of the Church, is a lengthy topic.
In the three ways we mentioned earlier-speech, understanding, and action-all things can be briefly summarized. Speech encompasses all the precepts of the heavenly oracle.
Therefore, "In many ways," he says, "and at many times He spoke," suggesting the forms of applying understanding regularly.
In the Gospel, after the resurrection, the Lord is said (Luke 24) to have opened the minds of the disciples so they could understand the Scriptures and to have kindled their hearts so they would preach what was revealed to others.

224
00:43:47,786 --> 00:43:56,854
They fulfilled what was lacking in Christ's afflictions in their own flesh (Colossians 1), and truthfully said: "We have become examples to all who believe" (First Thessalonians 1).

225
00:43:56,854 --> 00:44:02,065
Likewise, "So that we might give ourselves as an example to you to imitate us" (Second Thessalonians 3).

226
00:44:02,065 --> 00:44:09,379
If they had not done this, they would sing the Scriptures retained in memory in vain, unable to penetrate with understanding or perfect in action.

227
00:44:09,379 --> 00:44:16,994
Since we've discussed the hidden ways of speech and understanding of salvation, let's now focus on those hidden in action with the opening of each seal.

228
00:44:16,994 --> 00:44:27,465
If the opening of the seal is the revelation of the sacrament, and its mystery consists of speech, understanding, and action, let's see how these three can be reasonably found, said, understood, and performed.

229
00:44:27,465 --> 00:44:34,279
For example, "Behold, I come" (Psalm 40), it is written about me in the scroll; by saying "I come," he foretells himself as yet to come.

230
00:44:34,680 --> 00:44:38,763
When asked who this is, he is understood as the desired one of all nations, Christ.

231
00:44:38,763 --> 00:44:46,437
This is especially true because he is mentioned at the beginning of the book of Psalms and Genesis: In the beginning, God created the heavens and the earth.

232
00:44:46,437 --> 00:46:25,221
In Psalm 104, it says, "In wisdom, you have made them all." To those who asked who he was, he answered that he is the beginning, as stated in the Gospel of John, Chapter 8.
When asked why he came, it follows: "To do your will, my God, I desired," from Psalm 40. He says the same in the Gospel of John, Chapter 4: "My food is to do the will of him who sent me."
We understand this from his expression around the hour of his passion in John, Chapter 14: "So that the world may know that I do the will of my Father, get up, let us go from here."
Therefore, the deeds of this sealed book are known to have been revealed when he taught that he remains one with the Father from the beginning, and being born of a virgin, he lived as a true man.
For the salvation of the world, he took on suffering undeservedly, rose again with a triumphant death, opened the tomb, and broke hell. When he ascended to heaven, he sent the promised Holy Spirit to the disciples, filling the world, acquiring a multitude of nations, and teaching that he is the judge to be hoped for in the future.
When he opened one of the seven seals, I heard one of the four living creatures saying with a voice like thunder: "Come and see." And behold, a white horse, and the one who sat on it held a bow, and a crown was given to him, and he went out conquering and to conquer.
First, as we have mentioned before, in speech he varies, to which understanding is joined, immediately filling the innermost parts of action, and what proceeds in action agrees with the word, and by the relation of understanding, which I want the attentive reader to observe in the other signs.
He said: "I heard one of the four living creatures saying: 'Come and see.'" What is one creature is the whole Church, which proclaims with a great voice of preaching, inviting the succeeding Church to faith: "Come and see," as stated in John, Chapter 1. "If anyone is thirsty, let him come and drink," from John, Chapter 7. "Approach him and be enlightened," from Psalm 34.

233
00:46:25,320 --> 00:46:28,995
Wake up, you who sleep, rise from the dead, and Christ will shine on you.

234
00:46:28,995 --> 00:46:32,721
(Ephesians 5)
Behold, a white horse, and the one who sat on it held a bow.

235
00:46:32,721 --> 00:46:37,000
A crown was given to him, and he went out to conquer, and he went out as a conqueror.

236
00:46:37,000 --> 00:46:43,998
This horse can be understood as the apostles and preachers of the truth of the Church, whitened by grace (Psalm 50), whose rider is Christ.

237
00:46:43,998 --> 00:46:50,292
Therefore, through the prophet it is said (Habakkuk 3): Because you rode on your horses, and your chariots brought salvation.

238
00:46:50,292 --> 00:46:59,405
He is also said to hold a bow, which is more aptly compared to the preaching of the word of God, by which the inner parts of people can be pierced to bring forth the fruit of faith.

239
00:46:59,405 --> 00:47:03,634
Hence we read (Psalm 45): Your arrows are sharp; mighty peoples will fall under you.

240
00:47:03,634 --> 00:47:06,252
A crown is rightly signified to be due to preachers.

241
00:47:06,252 --> 00:47:10,884
And when he opened the second seal, I heard the second living creature saying: Come and see.

242
00:47:10,884 --> 00:47:18,587
The same words of exhortation to come and see are repeated in a different context, when the white horse signifies good, but the red horse is set in evil.

243
00:47:18,587 --> 00:47:25,233
I believe that just as good promises joy for the Church's victory, so evil warns of caution from the foreknowledge of future events.

244
00:47:25,233 --> 00:47:34,749
For it follows, another red horse came out, and to him who sat on it was given the power to take peace from the earth, and for people to kill each other, and a great sword was given to him.

245
00:47:34,749 --> 00:47:47,135
This red horse, as if stained with the blood of others, not its own, is said to oppose the victorious Church, when peace, which surpasses all understanding, is suggested to be taken from the earth, which is taught both by action and by the sword.

246
00:47:47,135 --> 00:47:51,666
And when he opened the third seal, I heard the third living creature saying: Come and see.

247
00:47:51,666 --> 00:47:55,442
And I saw a black horse, and the one who sat on it had a scale in his hand.

248
00:47:55,442 --> 00:48:00,879
In this scale, the measures of a feigned examination are signified, by which the merits of each are weighed.

249
00:48:00,879 --> 00:48:03,598
For whatever befits a just judge, transgressors usurp.

250
00:48:03,598 --> 00:48:06,820
Hence it is said: I will set my throne in the north (Isaiah 14).

251
00:48:06,820 --> 00:48:13,013
And because they could prevail temporarily with God's permission, it teaches in this way: Do not harm the wine and the oil.

252
00:48:13,920 --> 00:49:35,655
And I heard a voice from the midst of the four living creatures, saying: "A pound of wheat for one denarius, and three pounds of barley for one denarius, and do not harm the wine and the oil."
In wheat and barley, the Church speaks, whether through the great and the small, or the leaders and the people. However, one pound is not less than three. Indeed, the same perfection exists in singularity and in the Trinity. Thus, the Lord, in Matthew Chapter 13 and Luke Chapter 13, speaks of leaven hidden in three measures of flour, showing that wisdom and teaching from a small amount sanctify all the people in the mystical number of the indivisible Trinity.
He also teaches that the price of wheat and barley is the same, even if one surpasses the other in merit; both are redeemed with the same price. Otherwise, due to the diversity of professions, I think the different numbers of one and three are set. In the denarius, eternal life is signified, which among many dwellings is common to all. So, even if through differences in merit one may be higher than another with a greater reward, no one will be older compared to another; there will be one immortality for each individual, and a common eternity remains for all.
In the wine and oil, therefore, the power of the sacraments is forbidden to be violated, such as the anointing and the precious blood. Hence, we read in Zechariah Chapter 9, "What is His goodness, and what is His beauty, but the wheat of the chosen and the wine that brings forth virgins?" And in the Psalm: "Wine gladdens the heart of man, and the face is made cheerful with oil" (Psalm 104).

253
00:49:35,655 --> 00:50:08,349
And when he opened the fourth seal, I heard the fourth living creature, saying: "Come and see." And I saw a pale horse, and the name of the one who sat on it was Death, and Hades followed him. Power was given to them over a fourth of the earth, to kill with the sword, with hunger, with death, and with the beasts of the earth.
There are two parts in the world, one of God and the other of the devil. But the devil's part is subdivided into three parts: paganism, false brothers, and those separated by open error or schism. Thus, there are three parts that fight against one. In this context, he now predicted power would be given to the fourth.

254
00:50:08,400 --> 00:50:11,575
This church, he says, will be tested by various swords of evil.

255
00:50:11,575 --> 00:50:16,364
This is also reflected in the number of angels, where against one good, he opposed three evils.

256
00:50:16,364 --> 00:50:21,859
With the sword - a red one; the second - a black one with scales; and the third - a pale one marked by death.

257
00:50:21,859 --> 00:50:26,093
The red sword signifies war, the black one famine, and the pale one announces death.

258
00:50:26,093 --> 00:50:31,890
While assigning each plague, he also foretells future plagues by numbering them, including the names of the beasts.

259
00:50:31,890 --> 00:50:45,955
Since it may be unclear whether the speech is literal or figurative - because the sword can be both physical and spiritual - the same applies to famine, whether it refers to the word of the Lord or physical hunger, and to death, whether eternal for souls or temporary for bodies.

260
00:50:45,955 --> 00:50:52,558
He clarifies that the fourth good one will be tested by these visible, temporal persecutions, to which three evil ones are opposed.

261
00:50:52,558 --> 00:51:48,463
For those who are called according to God's will (from the Letter to the Ephesians), will remain in the fullness of the chosen ones, especially those whom he wished the sacraments of wine and oil to be kept unharmed, saying: "Do not harm the wine and oil." In the wine, he signifies the price of redemption, and in the oil, the chrism of baptism.
By mentioning barley and wheat, he shows that the church, up to the end of the world, cannot be destroyed by any persecution of evil, because he counts these species not insignificantly, but with a sacred number and quantity of value. What those exercise for their own malevolent punishment, God, supremely good, turns to the benefit of his own, providing us with opportunities for spiritual triumphs.
Then follows: "And when he had opened the fifth seal, I saw under the altar of God the souls of those who had been slain for the word of God and their testimony; and they cried out with a loud voice, saying: 'How long, O Lord, holy and true, will you not judge and avenge our blood on those who dwell on the earth?' And white robes were given to each of them."

262
00:51:48,816 --> 00:52:01,261
Of course, regarding those others whom God, even amid adversities, keeps safe through the secret work of His counsel, it is said that He has seen the relics of the martyrs-that is, their souls-not in a cheap or random place, but under the altar of God.

263
00:52:01,261 --> 00:52:09,755
This means that whether they remain in the unity of the Church or valiantly fight under the testimony of Christ's name, they do so as if under the altar of God until death.

264
00:52:09,755 --> 00:52:14,743
As was said about the Maccabees, under the covenant of God: Blessed are the dead who die in the Lord.

265
00:52:14,743 --> 00:52:24,028
Much more so for those who, knowing they have a home not made by hands, eternal in the heavens, desire their heavenly dwelling (Second Corinthians 5), they are therefore said to intercede.

266
00:52:24,028 --> 00:52:31,337
We conjecture in this way: after the Lord's passion has freed the groans of hell, we do not believe that the souls of the saints go to hell anymore.

267
00:52:31,337 --> 00:52:37,115
I think this is more aptly signified here, similar to the Old Testament, where the golden altar was described inside.

268
00:52:37,115 --> 00:52:58,400
Here, through the term of the memorable altar, the intellectual secret is known, like the inner Holy of Holies, where pilgrims, having received the pledge of salvation, sigh, having hope as an anchor for the soul, safe and firm, and going beyond the veil, where Jesus, the forerunner, has entered for us, according to the Apostle's saying (Hebrews 6), who thus indicated the presence of Christ by intention, to explain the figures.

269
00:52:58,400 --> 00:53:03,537
How long, O holy and true Lord, will You not judge and avenge our blood on those who dwell on the earth?

270
00:53:03,537 --> 00:53:14,303
This should not be believed in a carnal sense, that they are inflamed with a desire for vengeance, since we know that even here, those placed by them, through the abundance of charity, also love their enemies (Mark 5).

271
00:53:14,303 --> 00:53:22,452
But it is clear that they prayed against the kingdom of sin, and asked for such things out of desire for that kingdom, of which we say: Thy kingdom come (Matthew 6).

272
00:53:22,452 --> 00:53:36,922
And we understand this to be revealed to them by the presence of divine wisdom, that the wicked are inevitably to be punished with eternal punishment, and that until the end of the age, with the fountain of heavenly grace flowing, many are still to be joined to the fellowship of holy martyrs.

273
00:53:37,416 --> 00:53:43,216
Upon receiving this response, they are filled with indescribable joy, which we believe is symbolized by white robes.

274
00:53:43,216 --> 00:53:56,117
Each one receives a white robe, meaning that through the perfection of love, which is infused into the hearts of believers by the Holy Spirit, they are content with this consolation and prefer to delay for the sake of increasing the number of their brothers.

275
00:53:56,117 --> 00:54:01,868
What they carry in their prayers, inspired by divine benevolence, is said to be immediately informed by a response.

276
00:54:01,868 --> 00:54:07,468
It is not right to believe that they desire anything against God's will, since their desires depend on His will.

277
00:54:07,468 --> 00:54:14,069
And I saw, and when he opened the sixth seal, there was a great earthquake, and the sun became black as sackcloth made of goat hair.

278
00:54:14,069 --> 00:54:23,120
The sixth seal represents the sixth age of the world, during the end of which the final persecution is announced, shaking the whole world with its violent impact like an earthquake.

279
00:54:23,120 --> 00:54:29,520
The sun and the moon, Christ and the Church, are said to be darkened because many will deny Christ during the final persecution.

280
00:54:29,520 --> 00:55:30,225
As it is said in Second Corinthians, chapter 4, "If our gospel is veiled, it is veiled to those who are perishing, in whom the god of this age has blinded the minds of the unbelieving, that the light of the gospel of the glory of Christ, who is the image of God, should not shine on them."
Hence it is said in Matthew, chapter 24, "So as to mislead, if possible, even the elect."
In this way, the sun is said to become black, as if Christ's works, power, or teachings are temporarily obscured, or His defense delayed, when the wicked are allowed to attack the saints.
Hence the prophet Habakkuk, chapter 1, says, "Will you remain silent when the wicked swallow up those more righteous than themselves?"
Concerning Christ Himself, we read in Luke, chapter 2, "Behold, this child is appointed for the fall and rise of many in Israel, and for a sign to be opposed."
Through Him, some achieve certain progress, while others turn away and fall.
The moon turning to blood signifies that the Church will shed blood for Christ more than usual, with a great clamor of persecutions looming.
Thus, it will shed its own blood, not the blood of others, unlike that red horse, which is described as red with the blood of others.

281
00:55:30,576 --> 00:55:35,367
The stars fell to the earth like a fig tree shaken by a strong wind, losing its unripe fruit.

282
00:55:35,367 --> 00:55:40,931
These stars represent those in the Church who, though considered among the elect, seem to shine temporarily.

283
00:55:40,931 --> 00:55:45,722
When the rage of persecution intensifies, they fall from their high status as if from heaven.

284
00:55:45,722 --> 00:55:52,523
This is foretold by the Lord in the Gospel, saying:
Matthew 24: There will be a tribulation such as has never been nor ever will be.

285
00:55:52,523 --> 00:55:58,860
And unless those days were shortened, no flesh would be saved, but for the sake of the elect, those days will be shortened.

286
00:55:58,860 --> 00:56:04,115
The Church is likened to a tree; the unripe fruits, which another translation calls large, are people.

287
00:56:04,115 --> 00:56:10,091
The shaking of the wind represents the agitation of persecution, through which people are torn away from the Church.

288
00:56:10,091 --> 00:56:27,402
They are compared to unripe fruits either because of their faithlessness, as those who turn back to a crooked bow (Psalm 78), preferring to return to unbelief after leaving the faith; or because of the immaturity of time, where the Church, seeking to bring forth their happy birth, suffers the sorrowful misfortune of their unhappy end.

289
00:56:27,402 --> 00:56:29,978
And the sky receded like a scroll being rolled up.

290
00:56:29,978 --> 00:56:35,026
Rightly, the sky (that is, the Church) is indicated to recede like an open book, not a closed one.

291
00:56:35,026 --> 00:56:37,808
For whatever is closed cannot be recognized by anyone.

292
00:56:37,808 --> 00:56:39,921
What is unrolled is immediately revealed.

293
00:56:39,921 --> 00:56:45,588
Thus, when this persecution is clearly discerned, it avoids and withdraws so that it is not seen by strangers.

294
00:56:45,588 --> 00:56:55,686
It is known only to those it can trust through the unity of the spirit, protecting itself from unknown and foreign people, hiding by the spirit of discretion so it is not betrayed when understood.

295
00:56:55,686 --> 00:57:01,353
Hence John says:
Do not believe every spirit, but test the spirits to see if they are from God (First John 4).

296
00:57:01,353 --> 00:57:09,648
And every mountain and island was moved from its place, and the kings of the earth, officials, commanders, the rich, the mighty, and every slave and free person.

297
00:57:09,648 --> 00:57:12,481
The Church is also symbolized by mountains and islands.

298
00:57:12,481 --> 00:57:15,006
For it is the city set on a mountain (Matthew 5).

299
00:57:15,006 --> 00:57:16,448
Therefore, we read (Psalm...

300
00:57:17,376 --> 00:58:39,965
Mountains surround it, and in Isaiah chapter 24, it says, "In the islands of the sea, the name of the Lord God of Israel." This predicts being moved from place to place due to persecution. The good move by taking precautions and fleeing, while the wicked, driven by treacherous will, are moved to worse, as it says in Revelation chapter 2, "I will move your lampstand from its place."
We consider the kings of the earth to be powerful, capable of standing firm in judgment by their own discretion. Magistrates, tribunes, the wealthy, and the strong-all these are understood in terms of their different roles and the quality of their strength. None are predicted to be free from the troubles of persecution, though no one doubts that the number of the chosen will be saved.
Every servant and free person: the free are those not bound by marital ties, while the servant is recognized as being bound by marriage. They hid in caves and among the rocks of the mountains, saying to the mountains and rocks, "Fall on us" (Luke chapter 23), "and hide us from the face of him who sits on the throne, and from the wrath of the Lamb, for the great day of his wrath has come. And who can stand before it?"
We understand the caves and rocks of the mountains as fitting refuges of the Christian faith. For it is written in Proverbs chapter 30, "The weak people make their home in the rock:" to which sentiment the Psalm also agrees, saying in Psalm 104, "The high mountains are for the deer, the rock is a refuge for the hedgehogs and hares." Here we also recognize those exalted in the Church being referred to as mountains, due to their eminent love of Christ's knowledge (Philippians chapter 3).

301
00:58:39,965 --> 00:58:51,098
The small ones, driven by the noise of persecution, seek the remedies of protection, said to seek the refuge of the firm rock; for wherever they flee among such mountains, they are said to flee to the rock dwelling within them.

302
00:58:51,098 --> 00:58:54,482
But the rock, as it says in First Corinthians chapter 10, was Christ.

303
00:58:54,482 --> 00:59:03,898
So when they are fortified by the counsel of those mountains, being covered by salutary advice and protective counsel, they pray that the mountains themselves fall upon them out of compassion.

304
00:59:03,898 --> 00:59:08,165
For each one is covered under the shade of that which encourages them with exhortation.

305
00:59:08,165 --> 00:59:08,802
Hence Isaiah.

306
00:59:09,048 --> 01:00:10,800
And then he said, "Go into the rock, hide in the hole in the ground from the face of the terror of God and from the face of His fury, when He rises to strike the earth."
He says this to those driven by severe persecution, encouraging them to seek refuge. The prophet seems to suggest that even in such unparalleled persecution, we should seek Christ and the refuge of the Church, the invincible head and glorious body.
What he says about the face of the Lamb sitting on the throne is to ensure that when He comes, He may find them steadfast in faith, not as reprobates.
Furthermore, we must pay attention to the type of expression that the Holy Spirit has wrapped in this book.
Up to the sixth seal, He kept the order. Pausing briefly on the seventh, He recapitulates the same; intertwining two narratives, and as if following an order, He concludes with the seventh.
But this recapitulation must be understood in context.
Sometimes He recapitulates from the origin of Christ's dispensation, sometimes from the Passion, sometimes from the middle time, sometimes about the persecution itself, or just before it.
Now, after describing the sixth, He returns to the origin, intending to describe it briefly and differently.

307
01:00:10,800 --> 01:00:12,144
Chapter Seven

308
01:00:12,144 --> 01:00:20,698
After this, he said, I saw four angels standing at the four corners of the earth, holding back the four winds, so they would not blow on the earth, the sea, or any tree.

309
01:00:20,698 --> 01:00:27,430
In these four corners, the Church in John sees the four kingdoms represented: the Assyrians, the Medes, the Persians, and the Romans.

310
01:00:27,430 --> 01:00:33,454
These kingdoms, with their power, suppressed everything, allowing nothing to breathe freely according to their own law.

311
01:00:33,454 --> 01:00:39,224
Therefore, he said, so they would not blow on the earth, meaning those inhabiting the earth, the sea, or any tree.

312
01:00:39,224 --> 01:00:54,764
The number four is used because of the four most well-known parts of the world, which are the four corners, symbolizing the four winds, according to Daniel, Chapter 7: Behold, the four winds of heaven were stirring up the great sea, and four great beasts came up from the sea, each different from the other.

313
01:00:54,764 --> 01:01:02,863
The Church is seen to be intermingled with the kingdoms of the world across all four corners and is known to have foreigners within itself and among foreigners.

314
01:01:02,863 --> 01:01:11,772
On the land, this diversity is seen in the provinces; on the sea, the islands; and on the trees, symbolizing a kind of forest, signifying various roles and qualities of people.

315
01:01:11,772 --> 01:01:16,125
Then I saw an angel ascending from the rising sun, holding the seal of the living God.

316
01:01:16,125 --> 01:01:23,566
This first coming of our Lord Jesus Christ is declared here, who is elsewhere called the Angel of Great Counsel, as mentioned in Isaiah, Chapter 9.

317
01:01:23,566 --> 01:01:29,033
Therefore, from the rising sun, according to Zechariah, Chapter 6: Behold, the man whose name is the Branch.

318
01:01:29,033 --> 01:01:40,372
And he cried out with a loud voice to the four angels, to whom it was given to harm the earth and the sea, saying: Do not harm the earth, the sea, or any tree, until we have sealed the servants of our God on their foreheads.

319
01:01:40,372 --> 01:01:49,939
He is said to cry out because by the power of his beneficial preaching, he restrained the opposing powers, so they would not oppress the world with their usual cruelty of unjust domination.

320
01:01:50,496 --> 01:02:01,166
In these kingdoms, where fervent idolatry reigned, even the power of the four harmful angels is thwarted, as if they were mere servants, by that voice:
"Repent, for the kingdom of heaven is near"
(Matthew 3).

321
01:02:01,166 --> 01:03:34,172
This is also acknowledged by some of the demons, who said to the Lord
(Matthew 8):
"Have you come here to torture us before the appointed time?"
About this coming, Daniel says
(Chapter 2):
"A stone was cut out of the mountain without hands, which struck the statue that was revealed to him, whose head was gold, chest and arms were silver, belly and thighs were bronze, and legs were iron."
In this statue, four kingdoms are designated:
in the gold, the Assyrians; in the silver, the Medes; in the bronze, the Persians; and in the iron, the Romans.
As Daniel narrated with the angel explaining
(Chapter 2), he continues:
"In the days of those kings, the God of heaven will set up a kingdom that will never be destroyed, and this kingdom will not be given to another people; it will crush and consume all these kingdoms, and it will stand forever."
The stone, having struck the four kingdoms, grew like the destruction of the unjust tyranny and became a great mountain, filling the whole earth.
Therefore, these four angels are now said to be restrained by power, so that the mentioned kingdoms would not be allowed to harm with their usual ventures, until the number of the elect known to God is marked with an inviolable sign; about whom the Apostle says
(Ephesians 1):
"He chose us before the creation of the world to be holy and blameless in his sight, predestining us for adoption to sonship through Jesus Christ."
Now indicating this multitude of the sacrament with an appropriate number, it follows:
"And I heard the number of those who were sealed, one hundred forty-four thousand sealed from every tribe of the sons of Israel."
This number signifies the entire Church, for the trinity is a quadruple ratio, as three times four, ten plus two times ten plus twelve times twelve makes one hundred forty-four.

322
01:03:34,224 --> 01:03:40,898
The city itself is described as being twelve stadia in every direction, with a perimeter of one hundred forty-four cubits in total.

323
01:03:40,898 --> 01:03:47,012
This mystical number signifies the innumerable multitude of the elect, symbolizing an infinite number with a finite one.

324
01:03:47,012 --> 01:03:51,750
Next, we see the designation of the number of the sealed, mentioning each tribe individually.

325
01:03:51,750 --> 01:03:54,451
From the tribe of Judah, twelve thousand were sealed.

326
01:03:54,451 --> 01:03:56,590
From the tribe of Reuben, twelve thousand.

327
01:03:56,590 --> 01:03:58,577
From the tribe of Gad, twelve thousand.

328
01:03:58,577 --> 01:04:00,666
From the tribe of Asher, twelve thousand.

329
01:04:00,666 --> 01:04:02,908
From the tribe of Naphtali, twelve thousand.

330
01:04:02,908 --> 01:04:05,150
From the tribe of Manasseh, twelve thousand.

331
01:04:05,150 --> 01:04:07,290
From the tribe of Simeon, twelve thousand.

332
01:04:07,290 --> 01:04:09,328
From the tribe of Levi, twelve thousand.

333
01:04:09,328 --> 01:04:11,570
From the tribe of Issachar, twelve thousand.

334
01:04:11,570 --> 01:04:13,760
From the tribe of Zebulun, twelve thousand.

335
01:04:13,760 --> 01:04:15,900
From the tribe of Joseph, twelve thousand.

336
01:04:15,900 --> 01:04:18,142
From the tribe of Benjamin, twelve thousand.

337
01:04:18,142 --> 01:04:23,747
It's not surprising that, when listing all the tribe names, he started with Judah and repeated the same names.

338
01:04:23,747 --> 01:04:27,007
The Lord Jesus Christ wanted to be born from the tribe of Judah.

339
01:04:27,007 --> 01:04:32,459
Here, the order of earthly generations is not followed, presenting Judah, who is fourth, before the eldest.

340
01:04:32,459 --> 01:04:38,930
This signifies the fullness of the elect with the determined number of the redeemed, directing our attention to this intention.

341
01:04:38,930 --> 01:04:44,687
In naming the other brothers, he did not follow the order of birth, placing those younger than Reuben before him.

342
01:04:44,687 --> 01:04:48,253
This can be seen in the comparison of the books of Genesis and Exodus.

343
01:04:48,253 --> 01:04:54,673
Judah, when interpreted, means praise or confession, as taught in the paternal blessing: Judah, your brothers will praise you.

344
01:04:54,673 --> 01:04:56,813
Reuben, seeing the son, or seeing the son.

345
01:04:56,813 --> 01:04:58,953
Simeon, heard sorrow, or name of dwelling.

346
01:04:58,953 --> 01:04:59,564
Levi, added.

347
01:04:59,564 --> 01:05:00,889
Issachar, there is reward.

348
01:05:00,889 --> 01:05:02,417
Zebulun, dwelling of strength.

349
01:05:02,417 --> 01:05:04,048
Benjamin, son of the right hand.

350
01:05:05,423 --> 01:05:08,401
Dan means judgment or judging of the Hebrews passing through.

351
01:05:08,401 --> 01:05:11,378
Naphtali means breadth. Gad means trial, girded, or a bandit.

352
01:05:11,378 --> 01:05:12,354
Asher means blessed.

353
01:05:12,354 --> 01:05:13,427
Joseph means increase.

354
01:05:13,427 --> 01:05:15,282
Manasseh means forgotten or necessity.

355
01:05:15,282 --> 01:05:18,454
We know that various virtues are present in each of the faithful.

356
01:05:18,454 --> 01:05:24,066
For example, one person might stand out for their fullness of saving knowledge, while another excels in gentleness.

357
01:05:24,066 --> 01:05:32,314
These twelve names are arranged according to the order and ranks of the gifts and the progress of souls, not by their birth order or their names when they entered Egypt.

358
01:05:32,314 --> 01:05:37,975
That's because the focus there is on the origin of earthly generation and their dwelling in Egypt during the Exodus.

359
01:05:37,975 --> 01:05:44,564
I made sure to add the order of their birth, along with the interpretations of each name, to show that this change wasn't made in vain.

360
01:05:44,564 --> 01:05:52,665
We also want to caution the young ones not to think this number refers to the deaths of the infants murdered by Herod (Matthew 2), as some misinformed people believe.

361
01:05:52,665 --> 01:05:59,107
To be brief, Herod is known to have killed infants from only one tribe, Judah, where he acted within his jurisdiction as a tetrarch.

362
01:05:59,107 --> 01:06:01,206
However, here all the tribes are mentioned.

363
01:06:01,206 --> 01:06:11,162
We will connect the meanings of their names to their tribes and fit them into the number to clarify the previously mentioned meaning of the fullness of the chosen, if we explore the secrets of this place.

364
01:06:11,162 --> 01:06:17,701
In Judah, both the confession of sins and the praise of virtues are clear, which suits the number of those sealed from the same tribe.

365
01:06:17,701 --> 01:06:22,093
In sacred writings, confession is not only related to sins but often understood as praise.

366
01:06:22,093 --> 01:06:39,419
Hence the psalm of the dedication of the house of David, which is the twenty-ninth:
"Sing to you my glory, and I will not be saddened; Lord my God, I will give thanks to you forever, and the Lord having no sin at all. I give thanks to you, Father, Lord of heaven and earth."
Reuben means seeing the son.
We know that works are often signified in the sons.

367
01:06:40,199 --> 01:06:49,988
To the children of light walking in the light, it is said: "You will see your children's children; peace be upon Israel" (Psalm 127), whose children are now spiritually taken up in discussion.

368
01:06:49,988 --> 01:07:16,497
And the Apostle also says (Galatians 6): "Peace upon the Israel of God."
Therefore, from the name of the tribe, the number of those sealed is used, who rightly see the Son. To such as these, the Lord says (Matthew 5): "Let your good deeds shine before others, that they may see your good works and glorify your Father in heaven."
Simeon means "he heard sadness" or "name of the dwelling." I think those are designated here, about whom the Lord says: "Blessed are those who mourn, for they will be comforted" (Matthew 5).

369
01:07:16,497 --> 01:07:23,890
For they hear sadness in such a way that they prefer to have it devoutly accepted here, sowing in tears so that they may reap in joy (Psalm 126).

370
01:07:23,890 --> 01:07:39,642
They do not place their intention on their dwelling here, but lift their hearts up where Christ is seated at the right hand of God (Colossians 3), desiring to be clothed with our dwelling which is from heaven, like Abel, who was waiting for the city that remains in heaven, whose architect and builder is God.

371
01:07:39,642 --> 01:07:50,909
Therefore, the name of the dwelling of Simeon is interpreted so that he hears both what is to be had here and what is to be expected by the faithful; because now is the time for mourning and longing for a better dwelling.

372
01:07:50,909 --> 01:07:59,066
Hence, the Lord was saying to the disciples: "You will weep and lament, but the world will rejoice. You will grieve, but your grief will turn to joy" (John 16).

373
01:07:59,066 --> 01:08:26,544
Levi means "added." This fits with what we read in Solomon (Ecclesiasticus 26): "The number of his days will be doubled," those who use the goods of this present life in such a way that they purchase eternal things with temporal ones, lest they be hindered by earthly things and deprived of heavenly ones.
We know that Job provided a praiseworthy example to them (Job 42), who rightly despised the temporal things he had long possessed, so that the number of his years and the amount of his substance were doubled for him, remaining added.

374
01:08:26,544 --> 01:08:35,619
Hence Isaiah (Isaiah 61): "In their land, they will possess a double portion, and everlasting joy will be theirs."
Issachar means "reward"; hence Jeremiah: "Let it rest," he says

375
01:08:35,975 --> 01:08:41,135
Hold back your voice from crying and your eyes from tears, because there is a reward for your works.

376
01:08:41,135 --> 01:08:49,700
Listen to the Apostle, like a spiritual athlete, not fighting aimlessly, who says:
Galatians Chapter 6: Brothers, let us not grow weary, for in due time we will reap.

377
01:08:49,700 --> 01:08:56,511
And hear the Lord Himself say:
Matthew Chapter 6: Store up for yourselves treasures in heaven, where neither rust nor moth destroys.

378
01:08:56,511 --> 01:08:59,349
We surely know that there is a reward for the faithful.

379
01:08:59,349 --> 01:09:09,617
This number is known even for this tribe, and by the judgment of the chosen and the sacrament of their calling, it is especially said to them:
Rejoice and be glad, for your reward is great in heaven.

380
01:09:09,617 --> 01:09:12,506
Matthew Chapter 5
Zebulun, a dwelling place of strength.

381
01:09:12,506 --> 01:09:21,226
Here, I believe, signifies the militia of those who, fighting spiritually in martyrdom, also with their bodies as a dwelling of strength, overcome the rage of the enemy.

382
01:09:21,226 --> 01:09:27,727
Divinely aided, recovering from weakness according to the Apostle:
First Corinthians Chapter 12, they become strong in battle.

383
01:09:27,727 --> 01:09:34,383
Therefore, celebrated for the title of their name and the effect of glorious virtue, they acquire the titles of glory as victors.

384
01:09:34,383 --> 01:09:37,118
Benjamin (Genesis Chapter 35), son of the right hand.

385
01:09:37,118 --> 01:09:50,791
It is not difficult to recognize those sons of the right hand, whom Truth, in the Gospel, figured by the name of lambs, saying:
Matthew Chapter 25: The lambs to the right, so that those strengthened by His right hand in this world may enjoy happiness in the future.

386
01:09:50,791 --> 01:09:53,681
Dan, judgment or judging of the Hebrews passing through.

387
01:09:53,681 --> 01:10:06,219
I think the judgment of those is meant here, who discern spiritually between the times of the New and Old Testament, so that they neither think the Gentiles should Judaize, nor believe anything should be mutilated to condemn the Old Testament.

388
01:10:06,219 --> 01:10:22,369
On this question, indeed, there was not only a dispute among the apostles themselves, as blessed Paul mentions to the Galatians:
Galatians Chapter 2, but also among spiritual men afterward, such a question arose, which, as we are known by this great name interposed, would have needed to be referred for judgment.

389
01:10:23,039 --> 01:10:32,787
Quocirca Dan, the judgment of the Hebrews passing by, signifies either a time or a type, symbolizing the actions of the Jews passing by, which prefigures the coming of Christ and the Church.

390
01:10:32,787 --> 01:10:36,686
Their actions are not to be referred to themselves but to something greater.

391
01:10:36,686 --> 01:10:41,355
As the Apostle says in First Corinthians 10, all these things happened to them as a figure.

392
01:10:41,355 --> 01:10:46,331
And in Second Corinthians 5, the old things have passed away, behold, all things have become new.

393
01:10:46,331 --> 01:10:53,616
This is in line with the earlier discussion about the same ceremonies, and all things should not be repeated unless necessary for explanation.

394
01:10:53,616 --> 01:11:02,235
Naphtali means breadth, as we read in the blessings of Shem and Japheth in Genesis 9: May God enlarge Japheth, and may he dwell in the tents of Shem, which means named.

395
01:11:02,235 --> 01:11:10,546
This is understood as referring to Christ, who is named throughout the world, so that at his name every knee should bow, in heaven, on earth, and under the earth.

396
01:11:10,546 --> 01:11:18,498
We also read that his name is poured out like ointment in Song of Songs 1, which commands that his name be proclaimed continuously and not kept in silence.

397
01:11:18,498 --> 01:11:24,808
Thus, we see the breadth of the fruitful Church in the children of adoption, whom we rejoice to see expanded by good works.

398
01:11:24,808 --> 01:11:26,911
Gad means temptation, girded, or warrior.

399
01:11:26,911 --> 01:11:30,810
As we read in Job 7, according to the Septuagint, this life is a temptation.

400
01:11:30,810 --> 01:11:36,505
It is fitting for the soldiers of Christ to fulfill his commands and continually fight against all temptations.

401
01:11:36,505 --> 01:11:47,022
He says in Luke 12: Let your loins be girded, and your lamps burning, so that we may restrain illicit desires and shine through good works, as he also says: Let your light so shine before men in Matthew 5.

402
01:11:47,022 --> 01:11:50,357
We must direct the end of good works to God, not to human praise.

403
01:11:50,357 --> 01:11:58,565
For this reason, his name is interpreted as warrior, acquiring the goods of the heart secretly and offering them to God for approval, not for human recognition.

404
01:11:58,565 --> 01:12:02,926
As he promised in Matthew 6, your Father, who sees in secret, will reward you openly.

405
01:12:03,695 --> 01:12:07,803
Therefore, a thief is called so because he hides from sight. Asher means blessed.

406
01:12:07,803 --> 01:13:37,199
I believe the blessedness mentioned here is the one the Lord speaks about in the Gospel, saying, Matthew 5: "Blessed are you when people insult you, persecute you, and falsely say all kinds of evil against you because of me," to designate the sacred number among the chosen.
Joseph means increase. The increase referred to here should be applied to the leaders and various members within the unity of the Church, especially those whom the Lord says, Matthew 25, will gain double from the talent of spiritual substance entrusted to them.
This applies to those who fulfill the vow of virginity or the promise of celibacy, which is not required but brings a reward when faithfully kept because they choose what is better by forgoing what is permissible. Hence the Apostle, First Corinthians 7, says: "I have no command from the Lord about virgins," or like Zacchaeus saying, Luke 19: "I give half of my possessions to the poor, and if I have cheated anybody out of anything, I will pay back four times the amount."
In the Church, if some emerge who act out of love for eternal life, driven by great devotion, they could rightly be associated with this name. Either because leaders with diligent effort double the money the Lord commanded to be given to the bankers, Matthew 25, so that upon His return He might collect it with interest; or when celibates, foreseen by divine grace, conquer the temptations of the flesh with the abundance of the spirit; or those who, from their own resources, offer more than just tithes according to the command, but a greater part.
Motivated by increased virtue and devotion, they strive not only to obey the command but also to commend themselves to God with superior acts of virtue, not to avoid punishment but to gain a reward.

407
01:13:37,199 --> 01:15:12,215
His name, Joseph, which means "increase," seems appropriate: Joseph was elevated among foreigners and known to have prospered successfully. He had a son named Manasseh, which means "forgotten" or "necessity," as he forgot the very harsh servitude and captivity.
Now, if we look at the order of their birth according to the meanings of their names, we don't find the outcome of the previous explanation. For instance, if we start with the firstborn, Reuben, which means "seeing a son" or "they see a son," and place Judah, who is fourth in birth order, it completely contradicts a sound understanding. No one achieves the peak of good works before beginning with confession because unless we renounce evil deeds through confession, we are not shaped by what is right and pleasing.
Therefore, to show that their order of names was not changed in vain but to signify and recognize the great difference between the rise of a blameworthy nature and the orders of saving grace, we follow the order of this book and briefly connect the meanings we have derived from the interpretations of the names, like this:
The perfection of our works of confession and divine praise follows naturally, as Judah follows Reuben, so that it is neither desirable to repeat things to be repented of nor reluctant to fulfill praiseworthy deeds where God is praised. Therefore, Reuben is added in this order, so that he who works may rejoice in hope, and those who see may attribute the worker to the praise of God.
Yet, because the body that is corrupted still burdens the soul (Wisdom chapter 9, verse 15), and we groan while burdened (Second Corinthians chapter 5, verse 4), and as long as we are in the body, we are away from the Lord (Second Corinthians chapter 5, verse 6), and through many tribulations, we must enter the kingdom of God (Acts chapter 14, verse 22).

408
01:15:12,215 --> 01:15:15,004
As it is written, Gad follows, which means temptation.

409
01:15:15,004 --> 01:15:19,291
I say, it follows not by the order of birth, but by the course of spiritual combat.

410
01:15:19,291 --> 01:15:26,780
Even such people do not lack the temptations of this present life, through which they are exercised in struggle and girded with a spiritual belt.

411
01:15:26,780 --> 01:15:37,264
They are not allowed to wither in idleness; for although temptation can come in both good and evil forms, it is proposed here to be understood in a way that it may be turned into virtue through good use.

412
01:15:37,264 --> 01:16:59,073
Therefore, to be recognized as one armed and fighting spiritually: "You have girded me," he says, "with strength for the battle" Psalm 18. Hence, we read in James 1: "Blessed is the man who endures temptation, for when he has been approved, he will receive the crown of life," just as Abraham shone when he was tempted. For although temptation is indeed evil, we rightly call those blessed who overcome it or emerge victorious from it.
Therefore, after Gad, Asher follows, which means blessed, according to the rule of truth received from the Lord who says in Matthew 5: "Blessed are you when people hate you, and persecute you, and say all kinds of evil against you falsely, for my sake." Secure in the faithful promise of this blessedness, they are not distressed but say with the Apostle in Second Corinthians 6: "Our heart is enlarged." And they sing in the psalm, Psalm 119: "I ran in the way of your commandments, when you enlarged my heart."
Therefore, Naphtali follows, which means breadth, so that not only do we not fail, but also, forgetting what is behind, we stretch forward to what is ahead, according to the Apostle. So that, bound only by the necessity of human condition, we do not make provision for the flesh in its desires. For our way of life, he says in Romans 13, is in heaven, and although there is a desire to depart and be with Christ, Philippians 3, we still carry this treasure in earthen vessels, Second Corinthians 4.
Therefore, after Naphtali, Manasseh follows, which means forgetfulness or necessity. About this necessity, the Apostle says in Romans...

413
01:16:59,279 --> 01:17:04,597
XIII) Do not cater to the desires of the flesh,
as you should not serve lusts, but attend to necessities.

414
01:17:04,597 --> 01:17:27,993
The prophet, longing for better things, prayed about this, saying Psalm 24:
"Deliver me from my necessities."
This applies to Simeon,
which means "I have heard" or "the name of a dwelling place,"
to make it clearer what should be expected here
and what should be awaited for salvation.
The joy of the heavenly dwelling will be given
to those whose spirit is sorrowful with fruitful repentance,
to whom it is also said: "Your sorrow will turn into joy" (John 16).

415
01:17:27,993 --> 01:17:44,756
Therefore, Levi is added,
meaning "added,"
in which we understand either those who exchange temporal things for eternal ones, as Solomon says (Proverbs 13):
"The ransom of a man's life is his wealth;"
or those who follow the counsel of the Lord (Matthew 19),
receiving a hundredfold in this age and eternal life in the age to come.

416
01:17:44,756 --> 01:17:48,554
This also fits with what is written,
that he who adds knowledge adds labor.

417
01:17:48,554 --> 01:17:53,871
Even the holy Job had tribulations added to him,
so that, once tested, he might receive a greater reward.

418
01:17:53,871 --> 01:18:40,714
And not without reason does Issachar follow in order,
which means "reward,"
because, as the Apostle teaches (Romans 8):
"The sufferings of this present time are not worthy to be compared with the glory that will be revealed in us."
It is more fruitful to fight where a reward is promised.
These things God works and perfects in the dwelling place of strength, which is called Zebulun,
when strength is made perfect in weakness (Second Corinthians 12),
so that the body, considered weak by enemies,
and through whose substance they try to bring ruin to the spirit, is found invincible with God's strength,
succeeded by the increase of the unfortunate, that is,
Joseph, which means "increase,"
and in this context signifies the increase of graces, whether you understand it as the double return of talents,
the increase of spiritual benefit,
or in the things offered by the faithful with religious devotion to God the Redeemer.

419
01:18:40,967 --> 01:18:47,157
To help you understand, all these individuals are placed here with significant order and interpretation of their names.

420
01:18:47,157 --> 01:18:51,787
They are set to be on the right hand of Christ, the eternal King, in the future judgment.

421
01:18:51,787 --> 01:20:25,623
Benjamin is placed last, representing the "son of the right hand," symbolizing the ultimate happiness promised as the perfect reward.
At that time, the last enemy to be destroyed is death, as mentioned in 1 Corinthians 15. Thus, each of the faithful may rightly be called a "son of the right hand," or it could refer to the entire Church, about which we sing: "The queen stands at your right hand in gold from Ophir, adorned with many colors," as noted in Psalm 45.
It's important to note that in the Apocalypse, Manasseh, who is not a son of Jacob but a grandson, is placed in the sixth position despite being adopted among the sons. Meanwhile, Dan, who is indeed a son and counted among the brothers in both Genesis and Exodus, is completely omitted here. This suggests that the Church, adopted from the Gentiles, rejects the faithlessness of the Jews in the sixth age of the world.
Manasseh, born among foreigners in Egypt, is placed in the sixth position due to the merit of adoption, highlighting its significance. Dan, however, is given no place, clearly showing that everything here is based on significance, not just transient relations. Dan's omission indicates the passing away of the time of the Hebrews, as the ceremonial laws of circumcision and fleshly sacrifices are no longer necessary. This is taught by the Apostle in 2 Corinthians 7: "The old things have passed away, behold, all things have become new," and similarly in Hebrews 7: "The former commandment is set aside because of its weakness and uselessness."
Given these facts, I assert that I do not oppose the words of the Lord, who showed that three parables of profession imply thirtyfold fruit for the married, sixtyfold for widows and the continent, and a hundredfold (Matthew 13; Mark 4; Luke 8) for virgins, or even martyrs.

422
01:20:25,728 --> 01:20:35,740
While in the field, the active service of the clergy, the contemplative leisure of the monks, and the wanderings of the laity symbolized different things, it seems they do not exceed the same number.

423
01:20:35,740 --> 01:20:41,175
However, all these modes can be understood in the same three, proven by sound doctrine and clear experience.

424
01:20:41,175 --> 01:21:01,503
From the number of monks, the order of the clergy, and the ranks of the married, many often exist who, by their confession, are praiseworthy like Judah, effective in their works like Reuben, strong in the trials of temptation like Gad, blessed like Asher, generous in works of mercy like Naphtali, forgetful of past wrongs like Manasseh, sorrowful like Simeon in the valley of tears yet always rejoicing.

425
01:21:01,503 --> 01:21:28,271
They long for the name of the dwelling in heavenly Jerusalem; and in Levi, who rejoice in the promise of present and future life, founded on eternal good with added temporal goods; and in Issachar, strengthened by the contemplation of future reward; and in Zebulun, who fight for Christ and lay down their lives; and in Joseph, who strive for the increase of spiritual substance and offer more than God's commandments either in virginity or from their own resources; and in Benjamin, who receive the right hand of eternal happiness.

426
01:21:28,271 --> 01:21:41,051
So, with the last enemy, death, destroyed (First Corinthians 15), God may be all in all, to the extent that the Lord Himself does not contradict His words when, elsewhere, remembering the eight beatitudes, He describes them with an admirable arrangement.

427
01:21:41,051 --> 01:21:47,643
He did not separate them from those three professions but taught that they can be found in them and shine forth from their members.

428
01:21:47,643 --> 01:22:02,386
In this, we can observe the understanding derived from the names of these patriarchs and appropriately align the names to the same ranks, not by the equality of number, since these are eight and those are twelve, but by the quality of understanding related and arranged opposite to each other.

429
01:22:02,688 --> 01:22:10,527
For the first blessing, Jesus called the poor in spirit, meaning the humble, who, filled with the fear of God, are saved by confessing their weaknesses.

430
01:22:10,527 --> 01:22:13,930
To them, it is said:
"Do not be proud, but be afraid"
(Romans 11).

431
01:22:13,930 --> 01:22:20,222
Therefore, it is fitting to understand the poor in spirit as those in Judah, through praiseworthy and truthful confession.

432
01:22:20,222 --> 01:22:46,524
Hence, Isaiah also says:
"On whom does my spirit rest, except on the humble and quiet and those who tremble at my words?"
The second blessing is assigned to the meek. The meek are those who, obedient to sacred teachings, believe without resistance what they hear and accept without criticism what they see handed down in the Church. They are fittingly symbolized in Reuben, which means
"seeing a son" or "those seeing a son."
The third is:
"Blessed are those who mourn, for they will be comforted"
(Matthew 5).

433
01:22:46,524 --> 01:23:43,460
This corresponds to Gad, which means "temptation" or "armed," placed third according to the previous explanation.
The fourth is:
"Blessed are those who hunger and thirst for righteousness,"
to which Asher, which means "blessed," is also compared in the same order.
Indeed, no better blessedness can be found than for a lover of true righteousness to be satisfied by its author, who replenishes without depletion, is sufficient for each, and remains whole for all.
In the fifth place:
"Blessed are the merciful"; Nephthali, truly meaning "width," is associated in the fifth order.
This signifies exercising works of piety in such a way that, with narrow greed removed, it always expands joyfully with generous liberality.
In the sixth place, it is said:
"Blessed are the pure in heart, for they will see God."
Manasseh, in his sixth order, which means "forgotten" or "necessity," also occurs here.
Manasseh, who was adopted from a grandson into a son, also represents the Church, to whom it is said:
"Listen, daughter, and see, and incline your ear, forget your people and your father's house"
(Psalm 45).

434
01:23:43,460 --> 01:23:55,374
Such people are also fit to see God with a pure heart, who, having forgotten what is behind and reaching out to what is ahead
(Philippians 3), say:
"With my mind I serve the law of God, but with my flesh the law of sin"
(Romans 7).

435
01:23:55,632 --> 01:23:56,824
Is this relevant to me?

436
01:23:56,824 --> 01:24:09,946
It seems to me that the cluster of grapes brought from the promised land by two men (Numbers 13) symbolizes two groups of people: the Jews, who had the cluster (meaning Christ) behind them, and the Gentiles, who always had Christ in front of their eyes.

437
01:24:09,946 --> 01:24:15,289
In the seventh place, it is said: Blessed are the peacemakers, for they will be called children of God.

438
01:24:15,289 --> 01:24:19,438
Simeon is matched to this, meaning he heard sadness or the name of the dwelling.

439
01:24:19,438 --> 01:24:25,662
Such people, already enriched by the abundance of wisdom, say: With those who hate peace, I was peaceful (Psalms 120:7).

440
01:24:25,662 --> 01:24:36,190
They are grieved with the same zeal as the prophet who said: I saw the foolish and was distressed (Psalms 119:158); and My soul was grieved because of the sinners who abandoned your law (Psalms 119:136).

441
01:24:36,190 --> 01:24:41,844
In the eighth place, it is said: Blessed are those who are persecuted for righteousness' sake (Matthew 5:10).

442
01:24:41,844 --> 01:24:53,254
To this beatitude, Levi is assigned in terms of order, but I think Zebulun for the meaning of the word, which is the dwelling of strength, where the martyrs of truth are designed to conquer the devil, naturally stronger.

443
01:24:53,254 --> 01:24:58,648
Even though the sense of Levi is not far off if the honor of martyrdom added to baptism is acknowledged.

444
01:24:58,648 --> 01:25:08,762
However, lest someone thinks these merits were given by human strength, it should be proven that they are by the gift of the one who divides his own to each as he wills (First Corinthians 12:11).

445
01:25:08,762 --> 01:25:17,839
The sevenfold operation of the Holy Spirit seems to be in harmony with each beatitude or name, as long as those desiring to reach the harbor of wisdom know to start from fear.

446
01:25:17,839 --> 01:25:21,158
The fear of the Lord is the beginning of wisdom (Psalms 111:10).

447
01:25:21,158 --> 01:25:26,396
Thus, the prophet starts with fear when listing, and anyone striving for perfection will begin there.

448
01:25:26,396 --> 01:25:37,755
Fear is therefore in Judah, to whom the poor in spirit are compared; piety in Reuben, to whom the meek are assigned; knowledge in Gad, meaning temptation or girded, to whom the mourners are connected in the third order.

449
01:25:37,755 --> 01:25:42,786
Fortitude is the fourth, Asher, to whom those who hunger and thirst for righteousness are suited.

450
01:25:42,786 --> 01:25:47,558
Counsel is assigned to Naphtali, to whom the merciful in the fifth beatitude rightly belong.

451
01:25:48,336 --> 01:25:55,823
Certainly, it is a guiding principle that whoever wants to be helped by a superior should first hurry to help those below them as much as they can.

452
01:25:55,823 --> 01:26:04,330
The understanding of Manasseh involves forgetting earthly things and focusing on divine matters with a pure heart, which aligns with the sixth beatitude of seeing God.

453
01:26:04,330 --> 01:27:36,834
Wisdom, however, is embodied in Levi, who is particularly suited to bear the "logium," the rational word, because solid food is for the mature. As it is said, we speak wisdom among the mature, which is perfected in the soul of one capable of divine contemplation, making it effective. It is as if an action added by God:
For whether we are out of our mind, it is for God; or whether we are in our right mind, it is for you.
This especially suits those from whose tribe priests were commanded to be legally appointed to the altar. These priests clung to God in such a way that they also considered their sacred duties for their neighbor, or rather, for the people.
For the Lord was born from both the priestly and royal tribes, Levi and Judah, reconciling earthly things with heavenly things. As stated in Ephesians chapter 2, He is our peace, teaching that He is both the true king and priest. Hence, Elizabeth, Mary's relative, is mentioned in the Gospel of Luke chapter 1.
Indeed, because Christ the Lord acquired the Church for Himself from both the circumcised and the uncircumcised, Jews and Gentiles, when He grafted the Gentiles as a wild olive shoot into the richness of the olive tree of the Israelite people, as stated in Romans chapter 11, the redemption of both peoples is clearly shown in the named and numbered tribes. Especially to remember the salvation of the Gentiles, it says:
After this, I saw a great multitude which no one could count, from every nation and all tribes and peoples and languages.
Those whom he had previously named individually, he now unites in unity, standing before the throne and in the sight of the Lamb. They were clothed in white robes, with palm branches in their hands, and they cried out with a loud voice:
Salvation to our God who sits on the throne, and to the Lamb.

454
01:27:36,936 --> 01:27:44,169
In their robes, baptism, and with palms, the triumph of the cross is hinted at, suggesting that they would conquer the world through Christ.

455
01:27:44,169 --> 01:27:49,233
The love given through the Holy Spirit, as signified by the robes, is also referenced in Romans 8.

456
01:27:49,233 --> 01:27:56,983
This multitude of the chosen, whom God foreknew and predestined to be conformed to the image of His Son, is foretold by the sign of the sacred number.

457
01:27:56,983 --> 01:28:05,767
Those who come from the nations also become Israel, just as the children of Abraham are called, not by flesh, but by faith, in that seed, which is Christ the cornerstone.

458
01:28:05,767 --> 01:28:22,972
The Apostle says in Ephesians 2: He himself is our peace, who made both one and broke down the dividing wall of hostility, in his flesh, abolishing the law of commandments expressed in ordinances, that he might create in himself one new man out of the two, making peace, and might reconcile both to God in one body through the cross.

459
01:28:22,972 --> 01:28:46,482
As for the palms carried in their hands, this signifies either the perseverance of good works in their hands, as we read: The Lord confirmed his arms in good work (Psalm 76), and, With my hands in the night before him, and I was not deceived; or it signifies the power in their hands, which they received to become children of God by adoption, as it is said of Joseph (Genesis 41): And the Lord had given everything into his hand, that is, into his power.

460
01:28:46,482 --> 01:28:51,700
And with a loud voice they were saying: Salvation to our God who sits on the throne, and to the Lamb.

461
01:28:51,700 --> 01:29:01,001
With great devotion and unceasing praise, they proclaimed that the Father and the Son reign on the throne, that is, in the Church, with the Holy Spirit reigning together with them.

462
01:29:01,001 --> 01:29:18,258
The order of these words is as follows: Salvation to our God and to the Lamb who sits on the throne, as we read in a similar expression in the Gospel of John 17: That they may know you, the only true God, and Jesus Christ whom you have sent; as if to say, That they may know you and Jesus Christ whom you have sent, the only true God.

463
01:29:18,672 --> 01:29:21,110
There is only one throne and one nature's power.

464
01:29:21,110 --> 01:29:28,223
The name of the lamb designates both the Father and the Son, just as when the Holy Spirit is named, both the Father and the Son are implied.

465
01:29:28,223 --> 01:30:49,002
In the book of Acts, we read: "Take heed to all the flock, in which the Holy Spirit has made you overseers, to shepherd the Church of God, which He purchased with His own blood." We know that only Christ shed His blood for us, making it clear that even when one is named, the entire Trinity is understood.
All the angels stood around the throne, along with the elders and the four living creatures. He explained what this multitude was by naming them, distinguishing the whole Church. He said, "All who are around Him will bring gifts," and they immediately fell on their faces before the throne and worshiped God, saying, "Amen." To show that the countless crowd standing before the throne was known to him, he identified them as the angels who fell on their faces and worshiped.
He did not mention the multitude, the living creatures, or the elders worshiping there, but only the angels. They are the multitude, the elders, and the living creatures; they fell and worshiped God, saying, "Amen." Therefore, we also read in Romans chapter fifteen: "Rejoice, O Gentiles, with His people, and let all the angels of God worship Him."
Therefore, blessing, glory, wisdom, grace, honor, power, and strength belong to our God forever and ever. By enumerating these seven virtues, we are reminded to seek understanding, as God wanted His Church to share in these virtues. When these praises are given to God, each individual acknowledges receiving them from Him. We must consider that what is named here is not exclusively divine attributes but also those God deems worthy to grant to the faithful.

466
01:30:49,104 --> 01:30:56,150
Blessing and glory, wisdom and grace, honor, power, and strength-all of these are shared by the Church of Christ, and we rejoice in them.

467
01:30:56,150 --> 01:31:06,591
While omnipotence, majesty, and eternity are attributes that only God has always possessed, these seven virtues are granted to all the faithful by Him, who gives them the power to become children of God.

468
01:31:06,591 --> 01:31:11,837
Therefore, if we acquire any good, we should truly recognize that we have it through God's generosity.

469
01:31:11,837 --> 01:31:14,820
It is fitting to prove this abundantly from other sources.

470
01:31:14,820 --> 01:32:13,814
For blessing especially suits the Church, as we read in Psalm 3: "Your blessing is upon Your people." He will indeed give blessing to those to whom He also gives law and glory, about which we sing in Psalm 89: "Let the favor of the Lord our God be upon us," so that with unveiled faces reflecting the glory of the Lord, we are transformed into the same image from glory to glory, as stated in Second Corinthians, chapter 3, being called by the name of light.
And wisdom, not the uncreated, co-eternal with God the Father, but the wisdom created in us and the angels, which, as the law distinguished, says in Ecclesiasticus 1: "Wisdom is from God, and was with Him always, and is before time;" and it adds about the created wisdom: "Wisdom was created before all things, and the understanding of prudence from everlasting."
And grace, about which it is said, "By grace you have been saved through faith" (Ephesians 2); and honor, about which we read: "Glory, honor, and peace to everyone who does good" (Romans 2); and strength, which Isaiah mentions: "He gives power to the faint, and to those who have no might He increases strength" (Isaiah 40).

471
01:32:13,814 --> 01:32:41,022
And one of the elders answered, saying to me: "Who are these clothed in white robes, and where did they come from?" And I said to him: "Sir, you know." And he said to me: "These are the ones who came out of the great tribulation, and washed their robes and made them white in the blood of the Lamb."
One of the elders or prophets represents the body, or the Church, as if the leaders were speaking to the lower members about the reward to be hoped for the laborers in the future, as the Apostle speaks about the Gospel in Romans.

472
01:32:41,280 --> 01:32:47,912
The justice of God, he says, is revealed in it from faith to faith, meaning from the faith of those preaching to the faith of those listening.

473
01:32:47,912 --> 01:34:24,457
And when the number of the faithful is said to come from great tribulation, it demonstrates what we read in Acts chapter fourteen:
"We must enter the kingdom of God through many tribulations."
Therefore, the Apostle also says in Galatians chapter one:
"Brothers, let us not grow weary, for in due time we will reap."
The number of the faithful is refined through the trials and pressures, just as oil is carefully produced by applying the weight of the press. Through the threshing of the tribulum, the threshed grain is gathered for storage.
That they are said to have washed their robes in the blood of the Lamb shows the reward of their efforts, so the labor of the mentioned struggle is endured equitably.
He rightly added:
"And they made them white in the blood of the Lamb."
As if to say: The robes that others stained through neglect, ignorance, or contempt after the grace of baptism, these made white in the blood of the Lamb, that is, in the grace of Christ, or even through the acceptance of martyrdom.
This merit should be specially assigned to those in the Church who shed their blood for Christ, making the robe of baptism clearer through the better honor of the Lamb's blood.
But if this grace is to be generally extended to all the faithful, it should be noted that anyone who is cleansed by the fountain of their Lord, fed with the flesh of the Lamb, and ignited by spiritual fire, is thus helped.
There are those who, even if they do not seem to have public martyrdom in action, are proven to have it before God in disposition.
Because of this, they are in the sight of God's throne and serve Him day and night in His temple. The Church, to which He has set ascensions in the heart, as mentioned in Psalm eighty-four, in the valley of weeping, in the place He has set, serves Him day and night, in both prosperity and adversity.
The Church is understood to be the temple because it is remembered to serve in the temple, just as the throne.
And it follows:
"And He who sat on the throne dwelt in them."
For the soul of the just is the seat of wisdom.

474
01:34:24,504 --> 01:34:26,313
Wisdom is Christ, and Christ is God.

475
01:34:26,313 --> 01:34:31,890
Therefore, they will never hunger or thirst again, nor will the sun beat down on them, or they suffer any heat.

476
01:34:31,890 --> 01:34:35,106
They will not hunger because they are fed with the living bread.

477
01:34:35,106 --> 01:36:15,257
He said, "I am the living bread that came down from heaven."
They will not thirst because they are filled with such a splendid cup. As the Truth said in John 6: "Whoever believes in me will never be thirsty," and also in John 4: "Whoever drinks the water I give them will become in them a spring of water welling up to eternal life."
The sun will not beat down on them, nor will they be burned by deadly heat. God promises something similar to His Church through Isaiah, saying in Isaiah 25: "A shelter from the storm, a shade from the heat." He proclaims the integrity of His sacraments to flourish in them, ensuring they cannot be tormented by any burning temptation.
For the Lamb at the center of the throne will be their shepherd. Earlier, it was said that the Lamb received the book from the right hand of the one seated on the throne. Now it says that the Lamb at the center of the throne will be their shepherd, teaching that the throne of the Father and the Son is one, because the Father is in the Son, and the Son is in the Father. In the midst of the Church, the whole Trinity, one God, dwells through faith.
He will lead them to springs of living water, and God will wipe away every tear from their eyes. This spring is signified in Psalm 36: "With you is the fountain of life; in your light, we see light." Christ leads His own by ruling Himself, providing the way, and revealing the homeland, fulfilling what He promised by the oracles of life.
Solomon, pointing to this spring, says in Proverbs 18: "An overflowing river, a fountain of wisdom."
And God will wipe away every tear from their eyes. As they said in Psalm 42: "My tears have been my food day and night." In the time of consolation, it is said they will be taken away. When the fullness of immortal joys is obtained, all sorrow can be consigned to oblivion. For behold, says Isaiah 65: "I will create Jerusalem to be a delight and its people a joy. No longer will there be heard in it the sound of weeping and crying.

478
01:36:15,408 --> 01:36:16,752
Chapter Eight

479
01:36:16,752 --> 01:36:20,654
When he opened the seventh seal, there was silence in heaven for about half an hour.

480
01:36:20,654 --> 01:36:25,533
In heaven, which means in the Church, this half-hour of silence signifies the beginning of eternal peace.

481
01:36:25,533 --> 01:36:28,924
He experienced part of this silence because there was still more to come.

482
01:36:28,924 --> 01:36:34,593
Even with the seventh seal, he couldn't see everything that was to come, allowing many things to be revealed more clearly.

483
01:36:34,593 --> 01:36:39,332
The silence was interrupted; if it had been continuous, it would have marked the end of the narrative.

484
01:36:39,332 --> 01:36:45,511
But the silence needed to occur again, and so the narrative fittingly resumes after my own silence, continuing in the following book.

